President Biden has appointed three members to the Council of the Administrative Conference of the United States (ACUS). Leslie B. Kiernan, who was sworn in as the General Counsel at the Department of Commerce, will serve as a member. Funmi Olorunnipa Badejo, Special Assistant to the President and Associate Counsel in the White House Counselâ€™s Office, has also been appointed. Nitin Shah, the General Counsel of the U.S. General Services Administration, is the third member. ACUS is an independent federal agency that brings together experts from the public and private sectors to recommend improvements to administrative processes and procedures. The agency aims to promote efficiency, participation, and fairness in federal regulations and programs.